channel.title: Compiler Telling Me I don't have the Proper Java
channel.description:
Okay, so when I edited the compiler file, put in what I need it says: "You do not have JDK 5.0 or JDK 6.0. Go to od Taharoks section for step-by-step instructions Link to download the latest JDK update"
Alrighty, so the above is what the error message is telling me word for word. The only problem is that I do have JDK. After looking at Google I tried JDK 6u11 JDK 6u14, and even JDK 5u09. So if you could help me out I'd really appreciate it.
Thanks Much, C. Negatory

item.title: Compiler Telling Me I don't have the Proper Java
item.dc:creator: @legend-scape legend-scape
item.description:
@legend-scape wrote:

edit the compiler & stick this in & try it. (:

@echo off @TITLE if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. :end echo Finished! pause exit
